│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                              │
│                                                                          │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                          │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                              │
│ The crash occurs when GVN tries to split a critical edge whose           │
│ predecessor terminator is an IndirectBrInst.                             │
│ BreakCriticalEdges::SplitKnownCriticalEdge asserts that edges from       │
│ IndirectBrInst cannot be split. In the provided reproducer, GVN marks a  │
│ block as dead due to a foldable conditional branch and then attempts to  │
│ split critical edges of its live successors, which includes an edge      │
│ originating from an indirectbr. This leads to the assertion and abort.   │
│                                                                          │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                  │
│ - The log shows the first transformation in SplitKnownCriticalEdge       │
│ during the GVN pass.                                                     │
│ - The backtrace points to GVNPass::splitCriticalEdges(BasicBlock*,       │
│ BasicBlock*) from addDeadBlock, which then calls SplitCriticalEdge(Pred, │
│ Succ, ...). The assertion in SplitKnownCriticalEdge explicitly disallows │
│ splitting edges from IndirectBrInst.                                     │
│ - The IR has an indirectbr in block 'ibr' with two edges to 'exit'. GVN  │
│ determines 'ibr' is dead and processes 'exit' as part of the dominance   │
│ frontier, attempting to split the critical edge from 'ibr' to 'exit'.    │
│                                                                          │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                  │
│ GVN's addDeadBlock unconditionally tries to split critical edges from    │
│ dead predecessors to live successors to simplify phi updates. It does    │
│ not special-case IndirectBrInst, but BreakCriticalEdges does. Therefore, │
│ when a dead predecessor ends with IndirectBrInst, the call to            │
│ SplitCriticalEdge(Pred, Succ, ...) hits the assertion. The correct       │
│ behavior is to avoid attempting to split edges from IndirectBrInst and   │
│ proceed with poisoning phi incoming values without splitting.            │
│                                                                          │
│ Specifically, in addDeadBlock:                                           │
│ - It gathers Preds = predecessors(B).                                    │
│ - For each P that is in DeadBlocks, if                                   │
│ isCriticalEdge(P->getTerminator(), B) it calls splitCriticalEdges(P, B). │
│ - This lacks a guard for IndirectBrInst terminators.                     │
│                                                                          │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                               │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp                               │
│ - Location: In GVNPass::addDeadBlock, within the loop that attempts to   │
│ split critical edges (lines ~3304-3314 in the provided snippet).         │
│ - Change: Add a guard to skip splitting if the predecessor terminator is │
│ an IndirectBrInst. This preserves the existing behavior for other        │
│ terminators while avoiding the invalid split.                            │
│                                                                          │
│ Suggested code edit for lines 3304-3314:                                 │
│                                                                          │
│ Replace:                                                                 │
│   if (is_contained(successors(P), B) &&                                  │
│       isCriticalEdge(P->getTerminator(), B)) {                           │
│     if (BasicBlock *S = splitCriticalEdges(P, B))                        │
│       DeadBlocks.insert(P = S);                                          │
│   }                                                                      │
│                                                                          │
│ With:                                                                    │
│   if (is_contained(successors(P), B)) {                                  │
│     Instruction *TI = P->getTerminator();                                │
│     // Do not attempt to split edges from IndirectBrInst; this is        │
│ unsupported.                                                             │
│     if (!isa<IndirectBrInst>(TI) && isCriticalEdge(TI, B)) {             │
│       if (BasicBlock *S = splitCriticalEdges(P, B))                      │
│         DeadBlocks.insert(P = S);                                        │
│     }                                                                    │
│   }                                                                      │
│                                                                          │
│ This ensures GVN never calls SplitCriticalEdge for edges originating     │
│ from IndirectBrInst, aligning with BreakCriticalEdges' constraints.      │
│                                                                          │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                           │
│ The crash is caused by GVN attempting to split an edge from an           │
│ IndirectBrInst, which is explicitly unsupported by BreakCriticalEdges.   │
│ Adding a guard in addDeadBlock to skip splitting such edges resolves the │
│ assertion failure. The fix prevents invalid splits while keeping the     │
│ intended phi poisoning and dead-code processing intact. Expected effect: │
│ opt -passes=gvn no longer aborts on functions containing indirectbr and  │
│ dead blocks; GVN will poison phi operands for live successors without    │
│ splitting the indirectbr critical edges.                                 │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                          │
│                                                                          │
