  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs when GVN
tries to split a critical edge whose predecessor terminator is an
IndirectBrInst. BreakCriticalEdges::SplitKnownCriticalEdge asserts that
edges from IndirectBrInst cannot be split. In the provided reproducer, GVN
marks a block as dead due to a foldable conditional branch and then attempts
to split critical edges of its live successors, which includes an edge
originating from an indirectbr. This leads to the assertion and abort.\n\n2.
Analyzing opt's Log:\n- The log shows the first transformation in
SplitKnownCriticalEdge during the GVN pass.\n- The backtrace points to
GVNPass::splitCriticalEdges(BasicBlock*, BasicBlock*) from addDeadBlock,
which then calls SplitCriticalEdge(Pred, Succ, ...). The assertion in
SplitKnownCriticalEdge explicitly disallows splitting edges from
IndirectBrInst.\n- The IR has an indirectbr in block 'ibr' with two edges to
'exit'. GVN determines 'ibr' is dead and processes 'exit' as part of the
dominance frontier, attempting to split the critical edge from 'ibr' to
'exit'.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nGVN's addDeadBlock unconditionally tries
to split critical edges from dead predecessors to live successors to
simplify phi updates. It does not special-case IndirectBrInst, but
BreakCriticalEdges does. Therefore, when a dead predecessor ends with
IndirectBrInst, the call to SplitCriticalEdge(Pred, Succ, ...) hits the
assertion. The correct behavior is to avoid attempting to split edges from
IndirectBrInst and proceed with poisoning phi incoming values without
splitting.\n\nSpecifically, in addDeadBlock:\n- It gathers Preds =
predecessors(B).\n- For each P that is in DeadBlocks, if
isCriticalEdge(P->getTerminator(), B) it calls splitCriticalEdges(P, B).\n-
This lacks a guard for IndirectBrInst terminators.\n\n4. Proposed Edit
Point(s):\n- File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp\n- Location: In
GVNPass::addDeadBlock, within the loop that attempts to split critical edges
(lines ~3304-3314 in the provided snippet).\n- Change: Add a guard to skip
splitting if the predecessor terminator is an IndirectBrInst. This preserves
the existing behavior for other terminators while avoiding the invalid
split.\n\nSuggested code edit for lines 3304-3314:\n\nReplace:\n  if
(is_contained(successors(P), B) &&\n      isCriticalEdge(P->getTerminator(),
B)) {\n    if (BasicBlock *S = splitCriticalEdges(P, B))\n
DeadBlocks.insert(P = S);\n  }\n\nWith:\n  if (is_contained(successors(P),
B)) {\n    Instruction *TI = P->getTerminator();\n    // Do not attempt to
split edges from IndirectBrInst; this is unsupported.\n    if
(!isa<IndirectBrInst>(TI) && isCriticalEdge(TI, B)) {\n      if (BasicBlock
*S = splitCriticalEdges(P, B))\n        DeadBlocks.insert(P = S);\n    }\n
}\n\nThis ensures GVN never calls SplitCriticalEdge for edges originating
from IndirectBrInst, aligning with BreakCriticalEdges' constraints.\n\n5.
Conclusion:\nThe crash is caused by GVN attempting to split an edge from an
IndirectBrInst, which is explicitly unsupported by BreakCriticalEdges.
Adding a guard in addDeadBlock to skip splitting such edges resolves the
assertion failure. The fix prevents invalid splits while keeping the
intended phi poisoning and dead-code processing intact. Expected effect: opt
-passes=gvn no longer aborts on functions containing indirectbr and dead
blocks; GVN will poison phi operands for live successors without splitting
the indirectbr critical edges.",
  "test_traj": [
    "diff --git a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp
b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp\nindex 7704e49c499d..68f09c04835a
100644\n--- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp\n+++
b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp\n@@ -3306,10 +3306,13 @@ void
GVNPass::addDeadBlock(BasicBlock *BB) {\n       if (!DeadBlocks.count(P))\n
continue;\n \n-      if (is_contained(successors(P), B) &&\n-
isCriticalEdge(P->getTerminator(), B)) {\n-        if (BasicBlock *S =
splitCriticalEdges(P, B))\n-          DeadBlocks.insert(P = S);\n+      if
(is_contained(successors(P), B)) {\n+        Instruction *TI =
P->getTerminator();\n+        // Do not attempt to split edges from
IndirectBrInst; unsupported.\n+        if (!isa<IndirectBrInst>(TI) &&
isCriticalEdge(TI, B)) {\n+          if (BasicBlock *S =
splitCriticalEdges(P, B))\n+            DeadBlocks.insert(P = S);\n+
}\n       }\n     }\n \n"
  ]
}
